$ Visual Studio Code: File -> Preferences -> Settings

*File -> Preferences -> Settings* allows to edit â†’ development/editors/Visual-Studio-Code/settings_json[`settings.json`].
-
By default, Visual Studio allows to edit `settings.json` in GUI editor. In order to edit the file directly, the setting
`"workbench.settings.editor"` must be set to `"json"` (the default being `"ui"`).

The â†’ development/editors/Visual-Studio-Code#vscode-shortcuts[keyboard shortcut] for *File -> Preferences -> Settings* is *ctrl+,*
